Senate Fails to Adopt ‘Fast-Track’ Trade Authority

-- B y   E r i c   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-09-20T22:49:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/senate-fails-to-adopt-fast-track-trade-authority-correct-.html
(Corrects vote total in second paragraph.)  The Senate defeated an amendment by
Senate Republican leader  Mitch McConnell  of  Kentucky  that would
have added “fast-track” negotiating authority for future trade
deals to a bill renewing a tariff preferences program.  The amendment, which needed 60 votes, was defeated today
45-55.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Martin in Washington at 
